When he legitimized his children by Madame de Montespan on 20 December 1673, Françoise d'Aubigné became the royal governess at Saint-Germain.[89]  As governess, she was one of very few people permitted to speak to him as an equal, without limits.[89]  It is believed that they were married secretly at Versailles on or around 10 October 1683[90] or January 1684.[91] This marriage, though never announced or publicly discussed, was an open secret and lasted until his death.[92]
